Water lilies have special meaning to me. When my nephew passed away last year, I printed and hand-colored them on envelopes for my sister. She also grows them in her flower bed and it’s amazing that they grow here in the Midwest.  It was nostalgic putting this card together, filming it, doing a voiceover without talking about what it means to me, and now seeing it again to share it with you. You probably don’t know that for me, this a process that could span 3-4 weeks (between making and sharing). I still get the lump in my throat seeing the water lilies, thinking of him, and simply remembering. Just a bit of personal information today as it storms fiercely outside this morning. Don’t forget to tell your love ones you love them, forgive them, and show them unyielding kindness.
